how to use call transfer on a single line phone stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how to use call transfer on a single line phone categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how to use call transfer on a single line phone search this site use call transfer to transfer a call from your phone to any other phone on the stanford system to transfer a call to another phone on the stanford system press link or flash you ll hear three beeps followed by dial tone the call is placed on hold dial the 5 digit phone number of the phone to which you want to transfer the call wait for the party to answer when you announce the call the original caller can t hear you if you receive a busy signal or no answer press link twice to reconnect to the original call press link or flash all parties are connected press rls and hang up note call transfer must include at least one person on the stanford system if neither party is on the stanford system the connection between the other two parties terminates when you disconnect phone services for faculty and staff stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
